
-- ircd-phatbox-3.2.0

ircd-phatbox is a fork of ircd-ratbox via the mannfred security-hardened
fork. See README.md for the full list of changes.

Highlights:
- Builds with C23 on modern clang and gcc
- FNV hash folding bug fixed (broken since original implementation)
- DNS resolver overhauled (32-bit IDs, hash-based lookup, UAF fix)
- Close-on-exec enforced on all file descriptors
- Windows support removed
- mbedTLS added as third SSL/TLS backend
- TLS 1.3 support
- Autotools regenerated for automake 1.18+ / libtool 2.5+

This release is based on the mannfred fork's main branch, which itself
builds on the ircd-ratbox 3.1-dev trunk (v3.1.0-beta1) with ~200
additional commits of security hardening and bug fixes.

